    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Species of small Eurasian maple tree native to Europe, the Balkans, and Turkey. It grows to 15-25 m in height, having low branches and five-lobed palmate leaves, used commonly in hedgerows.</Note_Text>
